jrigby.openstack_queue.server

Interface ResourceProvisioningCallback

  • All Known Implementing Classes:
    ThreeStageJobCallback, ThreeStageJobCallbackImpl

    public interface ResourceProvisioningCallback
    Provides callback methods once resources have been created in the cloud.
    Author:
    jason

    • Method Summary

      Methods 
      Modifier and Type Method and Description
      boolean onFailure(Throwable e)
      Called if the resources could not be created.
      void onSuccess(ServerCollection nodes)
      Called if the resources have been successfully created.

    • Method Detail

      • onSuccess

        void onSuccess(ServerCollection nodes)
        Called if the resources have been successfully created. Classes implementing this interface must take care to close the server collection in order to free up resources for subsequent requests.
        Parameters:
        nodes - a collection of all servers created for this request

      • onFailure

        boolean onFailure(Throwable e)
        Called if the resources could not be created.
        Parameters:
        e - the exception that caused the request to fail
        Returns:
        true if the job is to be rescheduled (i.e. on a temporary failure) or false if the job is to be abandoned
